#Coding Portfolio — Labs + Fullstack App

This repository contains my programming labs, algorithm practice, and a full-stack image filter web app.

It shows my progress in Python, web development, and backend systems.

---

#  What’s inside

## Python Labs

### Lab 1B — Simple Calculator
A command-line calculator that supports:
- Addition
- Subtraction
- Multiplication
- Division (with error handling)

Focus: functions, conditionals, error handling.

---

### Lab 1C — Maximum Subarray
Finds the largest sum of any contiguous subarray.

Focus:
- algorithms
- edge cases
- debugging broken logic

---

### Lab 1D — Two Sum Problem
Returns indices of two numbers that add up to a target value.

Focus:
- hash maps
- optimization
- problem solving (LeetCode-style)

---

## Full-Stack Web App (Filter Fun)

A web app that lets users:
- Upload images
- Apply filters (grayscale, blur, sepia, invert, etc.)
- Preview changes in real time
- Save images to a gallery

### Tech used:
- TypeScript
- React frontend
- Node.js + Express backend
- PostgreSQL (via Drizzle ORM)

---

## Web App Features

- Image upload system
- Live CSS filter preview
- Gallery system (stored images)
- Download option for edited images
- Clean UI with responsive design

---

##  What this project demonstrates

- Python fundamentals
- Data structures and algorithms
- Full-stack development
- API design
- Frontend UI work
- Working with databases
- Debugging and problem solving

---

##  How to run

### Python labs:
Run each file individually:

python lab_1b.py
python lab_1c.py
python lab_1d.py


### Web app:

npm install
npm run dev


